name: Maura Healey
tweet: "Buy-now-pay-later" loans can sound too good to be true. Often, they are. Borrowers get caught in cycles of debt, paying more money in deals they can't get out of.  I'm joining a coalition of AGs calling on the @CFPB to take a hard look at these lenders and their practices.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: National Grid could've saddled families with millions in extra costs with the sale of Narragansett Electric. We made sure folks won’t have to pay these costs and secured nearly $13M in credits and debt relief. Utility costs are already high, and this is a win for MA customers.  https://t.co/wNppNPyfVK

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Congratulations to the cast and crew of #CODA! This is one amazing and inspiring film elevating the deaf community and showcasing our own Gloucester. Go see it.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Compassionate Homecare falsely billed MassHealth for services that were not properly authorized, stealing hundreds of thousands of dollars away from folks who rely on the program. This is a win for MassHealth, its members, and workers who deserve to be paid back for missed wages.

tweet: Los estafadores de inmigración como George Maroun atraen las personas con falsas promesas de tarjetas verdes o legalización. Luego, amenazan con deportación para que los clientes paguen.   Anunciamos que ganamos más de $240,000 en multas y restitución para las víctimas afectadas.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Informing residents about fraudulent law practices is part of our ongoing efforts to advocate for immigrant communities.  To report an immigration scam, call our Civil Rights Division at (617) 963-2917 or visit  https://t.co/lb5rTL1wjJ  https://t.co/fIM7x6LfJG

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Immigration scammers like George Maroun lure people in with false promises of green cards or legalization. Then, they threaten deportation to get clients to pay up.  We just announced that we won over $240K in penalties and restitution for those harmed by his illegal services.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Kids are struggling to quit vaping. Youth nicotine addiction is an epidemic — we need the FDA to protect our kids and stop e-cigarette companies from illegally marketing and selling these dangerous products.   https://t.co/pUBZEeDaNC

name: Maura Healey
tweet: It's been 12 years since the Affordable Care Act became law. The stream of attacks on the ACA has been almost endless, but we fought back — and we won. My office will keep advocating for high-quality, affordable care for people in Massachusetts and across the country.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Secretary Albright inspired a generation of future leaders, especially women and girls, to enter public service. A brilliant diplomat and a champion of human rights, she will be sorely missed. My thoughts are with her family and loved ones.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Yesterday, we filed a response to the @EPA's proposal for evaluating toxic chemical risks to neighborhoods next to known sources of pollution. We're pushing the agency to do its duty under #TSCA to better protect those most at risk.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: Tough guy white supremacists hiding behind masks and shades. Ignorant, un-American, and hateful.    I can only imagine what my Irish grandmothers would say.   https://t.co/LkaaWozvnu

name: Maura Healey
tweet: 50 years after it was sent to the states for ratification, women are still waiting for the Equal Rights Amendment to be certified. There shouldn't be a deadline on equality — it's time to enshrine women's rights in the Constitution.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: These are difficult times for our beloved local papers. These outlets are integral to government accountability and building a sense of community. It’s why I called on Congress to pass the Local Journalism Sustainability Act to support local journalism.

tweet: We must do more to listen to, empower, and protect survivors. To report a hate crime, contact your local police department. If you've witnessed or experienced bias-motivated threats, harassment or violence, call 1-800-994-3228 or file a complaint with us  https://t.co/V03XtI0unO

name: Maura Healey
tweet: One year ago, a gunman in Atlanta took the lives of 8 people, 6 of them Asian women, in a shooting spree motivated by anti-Asian hate and misogyny. My thoughts are with the friends, families, and communities of those lost on this painful anniversary. #StopAsianHate  https://t.co/Uat0kyvBKm

tweet: This week is Say Something week. name: Maura Healey
tweet: Equal Pay Day marks how long women have to work to catch up to what men made the year before. That’s on average—Black women and Latinas have to work even longer.   My work has always been about standing up for opportunity and equality. We must close the wage gap once and for all.
